						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Hero-stone set up near the temple of Kālēśvara.</hi></p>						

						<p>Kannara—A.D. 1258.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is dated in the <hi rend="bold">13th year</hi> of the reign of <hi rend="bold">Kaṁdhāradēva, Kāḷayukta, Vais11ākha śu. 3, Sunday,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1258, May 7, Sunday, f.d.t. ·45.</hi></p>						

						<p>It states that <hi rend="bold">Kētōja,</hi> son of <hi rend="bold">Bommōja,</hi> a blacksmith, died in a fight when <hi rend="italic">Manneya</hi> <hi rend="bold">Jōyidēva</hi> attacked <hi rend="bold">Hānugali,</hi> which was being governed by <hi rend="italic">Paramavis11vāsi</hi> <hi rend="bold">Rāghava-Nāyaka.</hi> <hi rend="italic">Sarvādhikāri</hi> <hi rend="bold">Chauḍi-seṭṭi</hi> is mentioned.</p>						

						</summary>
